 


1. initialize the git
	git init

2. set userName
	 git config --global user.name "mamun"


3. set email 
	git config --global user.email "mamun@gmail.com"

4. see setting username and email
	git config --list

5. show git status / unstage positiono
	git status
	
6. staging single the file 
	git add 'fileName.ex'

7. staging the all file at once
	git add --all
	git add .

8 commit the file / store in local repository
	git commit 
    press i and add text then :x and enter

9. commit in a short way
	git commit -m "message"

10. see all the commit 
	git log

11. minimize of git log
	git log --oneline

12. Back to previous state
	git checkout serialNumber

13  Back to master
	git checkout master

14 see the latest changes
	git diff

15. find diffrence between two commit
	git diff commitNumber1	commitNumber2

16. see difference after stage
	git diff -- staged

17. remove a file
	git rm filename.ex

18. remove from staging area
	git reset fileName.ex

19. connect local repository to remote repository
	 follow repository instruction

20. connect using ssh key 

    follow 


21  git fetch

22  git pull



============ BRANCH Commands ========== 

1. create a branch
	git branch firstBranch

2. show branch 
	git branch 

3. switch to another branch
	git checkout BranchName
	
4. Create a new branch and switch
	git checkout -b branchName
		
6. delete a branch (we have to switch another branch)
  	git branch -D test_branch

7  rename the branch 
  	git branch -m oldName newName

5. merging with master branch (keep the history of the all commit)
	git merge branchName

8. Rebase (move to the all commit into one branch). have to rebase from both branch ( ref : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f1wnYdLEpgI)
	git rebase master
	git rebase newBranch
	

============ STASH Commands ========== 
	
1.  Save code into temporary file
	git stash

2. Back to last stash (stash is stack)
	git stash pop

3. Show all stash
	git stash list

4. Go into a particular Stash
	git stash pop stash@{2}      // 2 is stash number
	
5. Clear stash list 
	git stash clear




============ Undo Commands ========== 
1. Revert is used to back previous commit. It does not remove the commit history
	git revert "commit id"

2. Reset is used to back previous commit. It removes the commit history
	git reset "commit id"

3. Ammend is used to modify most recent commit 
	git commit --amend -m "Added lines to README.md"


============ REMOTE Commands ========== 
1. Check repository 
	git remote -v






